Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov (R) and Ukraine's Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba (back) attending Russia-Turkiye-Ukraine tripartite Foreign Ministers meeting in Antalya, Turkey on March 10. Photo: AFPRussian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov accused Western countries of waging a "total war" on Russia and its people and culture as Moscow pushes on with its military operation in Ukraine."The West has declared war on us, on the whole Russian world," Lavrov said at a ministry meeting on Friday. "The culture of canceling Russia and everything connected with our country is already reaching the point of absurdity."